Sentencas: Ethane and electrical power are co-generated in proton ceramic fuel cell reactors having Cr2O3 nanoparticles as anode catalyst, BaCe0.8Y0.15Nd0.05O3-delta (BCYN) perovskite oxide as proton conducting ceramic electrolyte, and Pt as cathode catalyst.
Titulo: Ethane dehydrogenation over nano-Cr2O3 anode catalyst in proton ceramic fuel cell reactors to co-produce ethylene and electricity

Sentencas: Cr2O3 nanoparticles are synthesized by a combustion method.
Titulo: Ethane dehydrogenation over nano-Cr2O3 anode catalyst in proton ceramic fuel cell reactors to co-produce ethylene and electricity

Sentencas: BaCe0.8Y0.15Nd0.05O3-delta (BCYN) perovskite oxides are obtained using a solid state reaction.
Titulo: Ethane dehydrogenation over nano-Cr2O3 anode catalyst in proton ceramic fuel cell reactors to co-produce ethylene and electricity

Sentencas: The power density increases from 51 mW cm(-2) to 118 mW cm(-2) and the ethylene yield increases form about 8% to 31% when the operating temperature of the solid oxide fuel cell reactor increases from 650 degrees C to 750 degrees
Titulo: Ethane dehydrogenation over nano-Cr2O3 anode catalyst in proton ceramic fuel cell reactors to co-produce ethylene and electricity
